{"id":6334,"date":"2024-10-13T16:21:50","date_gmt":"2024-10-13T16:21:50","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/gei.thomsuninfocare.com\/?p=6334"},"modified":"2025-01-16T11:17:13","modified_gmt":"2025-01-16T11:17:13","slug":"dr-kiran-chandran","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.giridhareye.org\/dr-kiran-chandran\/","title":{"rendered":"Dr. Kiran Chandran"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-1 fusion-flex-container has-pattern-background has-mask-background nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"--awb-border-radius-top-left:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-left:0px;--awb-flex-wrap:wrap;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row fusion-flex-align-items-flex-start fusion-flex-content-wrap\" style=\"max-width:1414.4px;margin-left: calc(-4% \/ 2 );margin-right: calc(-4% \/ 2 );\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-0 fusion_builder_column_1_1 1_1 fusion-flex-column\" style=\"--awb-padding-top:40px;--awb-padding-bottom:50px;--awb-bg-size:cover;--awb-width-large:100%;--awb-margin-top-large:0px;--awb-spacing-right-large:1.92%;--awb-margin-bottom-large:20px;--awb-spacing-left-large:1.92%;--awb-width-medium:100%;--awb-order-medium:0;--awb-spacing-right-medium:1.92%;--awb-spacing-left-medium:1.92%;--awb-width-small:100%;--awb-order-small:0;--awb-spacing-right-small:1.92%;--awb-spacing-left-small:1.92%;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-column-has-shadow fusion-flex-justify-content-flex-start fusion-content-layout-column\"><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-1 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Educational Qualifications<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-1\"><p>Dr. Kiran Chandran completed his MBBS at KMC Manipal in 2015, followed by an MS in Ophthalmology at the same institution in 2019. He further advanced his expertise with a short-term Medical Retina fellowship at Giridhar Eye Institute in 2020, and a long-term Fellowship in Medical Retina from 2020 to 2021.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-2 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:40px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Specialisation<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-2\"><p>Dr. Kiran specializes in Ophthalmology, with a focus on Retina and Uvea. His primary interests include retinal and uveal diagnostics, where he excels in performing and interpreting various investigative procedures such as fundus fluorescein angiography, indocyanine green angiography, optical coherence tomography (OCT), OCT-Angiography, fundus autofluorescence, and ultrasound B-scan. He is also skilled in laser procedures (including pan-retinal photocoagulation, barrage laser, and focal laser) and administering intravitreal injections (anti-VEGF, steroids, and antibiotics). His special areas of interest encompass Age-Related Macular Degeneration, Polypoidal Choroidal Vasculopathy, Macular Telangiectasia Type-2, Diabetic Retinopathy, and Posterior Uveitis.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-3 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:40px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Work Experience<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-3\"><p>Dr. Kiran\u2019s career has been primarily associated with Giridhar Eye Institute. He served as a Research Associate from June 2021 to March 2022, progressed to Associate Consultant in Retina from April 2022 to August 2024, and currently holds the position of Consultant in Retina since September 2024.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-4 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:40px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Publications<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-4\"><p>Dr. Kiran Chandran is a distinguished contributor to the field of ophthalmology with a robust portfolio of both international and national publications, alongside notable chapters in key medical texts. His research primarily focuses on intricate areas of macular diseases, showcasing significant findings and innovative imaging techniques.<\/p>\n<p><strong>International Publications:<\/strong><\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Bilateral simultaneous Central Retinal Artery Occlusion (CRAO) in a patient with Systemic Lupus Erythematosus (SLE) \u2013 <em>Am J Ophthalmol Case Rep<\/em>, 2020 Jul 20;19:100833.<\/li>\n<li>Microvascular changes precede visible neurodegeneration in fellow eyes of patients with asymmetric type 2 macular telangiectasia \u2013 <em>Eye (Lond)<\/em>, 2022 Aug;36(8):1623-1630.<\/li>\n<li>Type-3 macular neovascularization in a case of long-standing macular telangiectasia type-2 \u2013 <em>Oman J Ophthalmol<\/em>, 2023 Jun 27;16(2):377-381.<\/li>\n<li>OUTER FOVEAL DEFECTS IN TYPE-2 MACULAR TELANGIECTASIA \u2013 <em>Retina<\/em>, 2023 Jan 1;43(1):111-119.<\/li>\n<li>Relation of interdigitation zone changes and right-angle vessels in Macular Telangiectasia Type-2 (MacTel) \u2013 <em>Eye (Lond)<\/em>, 2023 Oct;37(14):2977-2986.<\/li>\n<li>Macular neovascularization \u2013 <em>Surv Ophthalmol<\/em>, 2024 Aug 31:S0039-6257(24)00095-X.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p><strong>National Publications:<\/strong><\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Utility of multimodal imaging in the detection and follow-up of retinal astrocytic hamartomas in a young girl with tuberous sclerosis complex \u2013 <em>Indian J Ophthalmol<\/em>, 2022 Jul;70(7):2725-2727.<\/li>\n<li>Relevance of multicolor imaging, its component channels, and fundus autofluorescence in describing macular telangiectasia type-2 (MacTel) lesion characteristics \u2013 <em>Indian J Ophthalmol<\/em>, 2024 Jan 1;72(Suppl 1):S125-S134.<\/li>\n<li>Tamoxifen maculopathy mimicking type-2 macular telangiectasia (MacTel-2) \u2013 <em>Indian Journal of Ophthalmology &#8211; Case Reports<\/em>, 2(3):p 722-724, Jul\u2013Sep 2022.<\/li>\n<li>Multimodal imaging of bilateral basal laminar drusen \u2013 <em>Indian Journal of Ophthalmology &#8211; Case Reports<\/em>, 3(1):p 216-218, Jan\u2013Mar 2023.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Chapters Published:<\/strong><\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>Current trends in the management of Neovascular Age-Related Macular Degeneration \u2013 <em>Recent Advances in Ophthalmology<\/em>, Jaypee publishers, Chapter 12, Edition 15.<\/li>\n<li>Multimodal imaging in Macular Diseases \u2013 <em>Recent Advances in Ophthalmology<\/em>, Jaypee publishers, Chapter 13, Edition 16.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-5 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-three\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:40px;--awb-margin-bottom:0px;\"><h3 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left\" style=\"margin:0;\">Achievements<\/h3><\/div><div class=\"fusion-separator\" style=\"align-self: flex-start;margin-right:auto;margin-bottom:20px;width:100%;max-width:20%;\"><div class=\"fusion-separator-border sep-single sep-solid\" style=\"--awb-height:20px;--awb-amount:20px;--awb-sep-color:var(--awb-color4);border-color:var(--awb-color4);border-top-width:2px;\"><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-5\"><p>Dr. Kiran&#8217;s accomplishments include securing a distinction in Ophthalmology during his MBBS and ranking among the top five candidates. He won the Sherlock Holmes Ophthalmology Quiz at KMC Manipal in 2018 and participated in various significant events, including the Teachers of Tomorrow program, the Asia Pacific VitreoRetina Society conference, and the European VitreoRetina Society conference in 2024. He has also been actively involved in the Smart India study on diabetic retinopathy and is a member of esteemed societies like the All India Ophthalmology Society (AIOS) and the VitreoRetina Society of India (VRSI). Additionally, Dr. Kiran is trained in Basic Life Support (BLS), Advanced Cardiac Life Support (ACLS), and advanced trauma courses. He is a <span data-olk-copy-source=\"MessageBody\">Peer Reviewer for International Journals in Ophthalmology such as American Journal Of Ophthalmology Case Reports, BMC ophthalmology, International Ophthalmology.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-fullwidt